args: Who am I? Am I Lathna?\nOr someone else?
There you are! I've been searching\nfor you everywhere.
Eek! Y-you're from Kyril!\nWhat are you doing here?
Help me, messenger! Take me to the\nAncient One's side while there's yet time!
I know who is truly responsible for all\nof the village murders—and it's only a\nmatter of time before he kills me, too!
So please, take me to the Ancient One's\nfeast before it's too late! I beg you!
Wh-what are you saying?\nWhat do you think I am?
You are a messenger of the multifarious\nAncient One—the savior for whom we have\nso long awaited.
We are disciples who worship the\nAncient One. And now, at long last,\nthe sacrifices are gathered.
I have now slain all of my brethren from\nthe village. Accept them, O messenger!
By offering them up as sacrifice,\nI—and I alone—will receive the full\nglory of the Ancient One's favor!
You killed everyone for YOURSELF?!\nDid you cause my scary dreams, too?!
It matters not! I beseech you, messenger,\nawaken and take me home at long last!
Awaken! Awaken and remember\nyour true name!
Now do it! Take me with you!\nTake me to the Ancient One's feast!
Unasked offerings are mere pebbles.\nBathetic offerings of no account.\nA pile of slaughtered, useless lambs.
Yours is the fancy of the deranged.\nFoolish. Unrealized. It shall burst like a\nreddened bubble. Ripple and vanish.
But why, Master Nyarlathotep? Why?!\nI offered gifts to the Ancient One!
I am a messenger, not a tool.\nI obey, yet plot scurrilous rebellion.\nI care not for the whims of a madman.
Your blessing is without mercy.\nSans salvation. Doomed to evanesce\nwithout meaning into utter oblivion.
To the sky! The sky! The sky! The sky!\nTHE SKY! THE SKY! THE SKYYYYYY!
I was talking to the village chief,\nand then... Where am I?
You're in the Halidom.\nDo you know what that is?
I found you unconscious by the side\nof a lake near the village.
So I'm...safe? The scary dreams are over?
You're fine. Nothing's going to scare you\never again.
Like I said, it wasn't you. The moment I\nentered the chief's home, I found a\nmountain of evidence implicating him.

He was gathering offerings for some
heretic god. I'd thought the murders were
for the purpose of eliminating witnesses,
but it turned out to be even more sinister.
Still, I'm surprised he moved so quickly\nfrom killing cats to killing humans.
Either way, the rest of this case isn't\nsomething for young ears.
Though I AM pretty upset about the cats...
Hmm? Is that another stray?\nHow'd you get in, little fellow?
Ha! Boy, he sure took to you fast.\nWhat say you try looking after him?
I'm sure we'll get along great.\nRight, Ulthar?
Is that what you're going to call him?
Of course. Because he IS Ulthar.
Hey, who am I to argue with a cat?\nTake care of her, Ulthar!
Never mind. I'm tired, and I think my\neyes are playing tricks on me.
Anyway, I'm going to head out. The folks\nhere said they'd look after you for as\nlong as you need, so no worries.
So what should we play next?

With that, my scary dreams came
to an end. I left the village of Kyril
behind, and began a life in the
Halidom with Ulthar.

All the people here are really nice,
and I'm convinced that the terrible
things from before weren't my fault.
After all, I haven't killed anyone
here—and Ulthar even came back!

I'm so grateful to you, my savior.
Grateful for everything that's
happened since I was born.
Thank you...O Ancient One.
